      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air and soak your <strong>skewer[s]</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking!)</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp – these are your <strong>herby fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679661315528-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679661315528-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679661315528-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679661315528-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679661315528-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>to a large bowl with your <strong>chicken thighs</strong>, <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the<strong> grated garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679661317970-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679661317970-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679661317970-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679661317970-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679661317970-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– these are your <strong>marinated chicken thighs</strong></p><p>Thread the <strong>marinated chicken thighs</strong> onto the <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewer[s]</strong> in a snake-like fashion – this is your <strong>marinated chicken skewer[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679661321094-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679661321094-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679661321094-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
