            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es] </strong>into rounds</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679661332005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679661332005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679661332005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679661332005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679661332005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated cucumber</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>remaining grated garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), most of the <strong>chopped mint</strong> (save the rest for garnish!), your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>tzatziki</strong></p><p>Put your <strong>gluten free</strong> <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in the oven for 5 min or until hot and crusty, then carefully slice in half before serving</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679661335570-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679661335570-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679661335570-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679661335570-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679661335570-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build your sandwich, fill the <strong>crusty</strong> <strong>gluten free brioche bun</strong> with the <strong>sliced chicken thigh souvlaki</strong>,<strong> </strong>a<strong> </strong>dollop of<strong> tzatziki</strong>, a couple of <strong>herby fries </strong>and a <strong>tomato round </strong>– this is your <strong>gluten free chicken thigh souvlaki sandwich</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>remaining herby fries</strong> to the side with the <strong>remaining chicken thigh souvlaki skewer</strong>, <strong>remaining tomato rounds</strong>,<strong> sliced cucumber </strong>and<strong> reserved chopped mint</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
